title: High Physician Density
description: In 2021, Cuba had 9.429 physicians per 1,000 people, indicating a robust healthcare workforce.

title: Complete Rural Birth Registration
description: As of 2019, Cuba achieved a 100% completeness rate in rural birth registration, ensuring comprehensive demographic data.

title: High Transaction Costs for Remittances
description: In 2023, the average transaction cost of sending remittances to Cuba was 19.63%, one of the highest globally, impacting financial inflows.

title: Low Merchandise Trade as GDP Percentage
description: In 2020, merchandise trade accounted for only 8.32% of Cuba's GDP, reflecting limited trade engagement.

title: Negative Net Official Flows from WTO-ITC
description: Cuba experienced a net outflow of $3 from WTO-ITC in 2020, indicating financial outgoings surpassing incomings.

title: Significant Male Contribution to Unpaid Domestic Work
description: In 2016, Cuban males spent 12.47% of their day on unpaid domestic and care work, highlighting gender role dynamics.

title: Minimal Net Official Flows from UNAIDS
description: In 2017, Cuba received $500 in net official flows from UNAIDS, reflecting limited financial support from this agency.

title: Residual Merchandise Exports
description: In 2023, residual merchandise exports constituted 4.05% of Cuba's total merchandise exports, indicating a focus on specific export categories.
